    • Constructor Detail

      • DoubleParam

        public DoubleParam(java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String title,
                   java.lang.String description,
                   java.lang.Double minValue,
                   java.lang.Double maxValue,
                   java.lang.Double defaultValue,
                   java.lang.Double step)
        This will validate each input. If one does not satisfy, it will bring the default value. Be careful of List. Should use a real provided class implementing List, not by wrapping.
        Parameters:
        name - Should be unique among parameters of a pattern
        title - no constraint
        description - no constraint
        minValue - defines minimum of range of selection. Default = Double.MIN_VALUE
        maxValue - defines maximum of range of selection. Default = Double.MAX_VALUE
        defaultValue - Round up by step
        • 0.0 if Double.isInfinite() or Double.isNaN() or null
        • minValue if lower than minValue
        • maxValue if higher than maxValue
        step - if Double.isInfinite() or Double.isNaN() or null or 0, step will be set to 1.0
        if negative, step will be the opposite value
